I"€<h1 id="discounts">Discounts</h1>

<p>We offer several discounts to people and causes we believe in.
Here are some of the most important causes we support.
You may only apply one discount at a time.</p>

<ul>
  
    <li><a href="#Open-Source-&amp;-Free-Software">Open-Source &amp; Free Software</a></li>
  
    <li><a href="#Small-Businesses">Small Businesses</a></li>
  
    <li><a href="#NHCA-Members">NHCA Members</a></li>
  
    <li><a href="#Community-Websites-&amp;-Services">Community Websites &amp; Services</a></li>
  
</ul>

<h2 id="Open-Source-&amp;-Free-Software">Open-Source &amp; Free Software</h2>

<p>Any software built and hosted entirely in line with either the <a href="https://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html.en">GNU</a> or the <a href="https://opensource.org/docs/osd">OSI</a> guidelines will receive a 10% discount.</p>

<h2 id="Small-Businesses">Small Businesses</h2>

<p>This is assessed on a case-by-case basis, and it usually caries a modest 10% discount.</p>

<h2 id="NHCA-Members">NHCA Members</h2>

<p>Members of the <a href="https://nhca.ca">NHCA (Northern Hills Community Association)</a> are eligible for a 10% discount.</p>

<h2 id="Community-Websites-&amp;-Services">Community Websites &amp; Services</h2>

<p>Anything which broadly comes under the umbrella of community services: community gardens, book clubs, church groups, etc. are eligible for a 10% discount.</p>

